speaker: ['#oedipus antigona']

speaker: ['#oedipus antigona']

speaker: ['#oedipus antigona']

speaker: ['#oedipus antigona']

perseus: animosa virgo:'funus extendi» meum

speaker: ['#satelles']
perseus: nisi sic videbo? iunge complexus prior,
anceps: ni^si^ si_c vi^de_bo* ju_nge^ co_mple*xu_s pri^o*r

speaker: ['#satelles']
perseus: qui tot labores totque perpessus mala
anceps: qvi* to_t la^bo_re*s to_tqve^ pe_rpe*ssu_s ma^la*

speaker: ['#satelles']
perseus: longo parentem fessus exilio vides,
anceps: lo*ngo_ pa^re_nte*m fe_ssu^s e_xi^li^o_ vi^de*s

speaker: ['#satelles']
perseus: accede propius, elude vagina impium
anceps: a*cce_de^ pro^pi^u*s clu_de^ va_gi*n(a) i_mpi^u*m

speaker: ['#satelles']
perseus: ensem et trementem iamque cupientem excuti
anceps: e*ns(e)m e_t tre^me_nte*m ja_mqve^ cu^pi^e*nt(e)m e_xcu^ti*

speaker: ['#satelles']
perseus: hastam solo defige; maternum tuo
anceps: ha*sta_m so^lo_ de*fi_ge^ ma_te*rnu_m tu^o*

speaker: ['#satelles']
perseus: coire pectus pectori clipeus vetat:
anceps: co*i_re^ pe_ctu*s pe_cto^ri_ cli^pe^u_s ve^ta*t

speaker: ['#satelles']
perseus: hunc quoque repone, vinculo frontem exue
anceps: hu*nc qvo^qve^ re^po_ne* vi_ncu^lo_ fro*nt(e)m e_xu^e*

speaker: ['#satelles']
perseus: tegumenque capitis triste belligeri leva
anceps: te^gu^me_nqve^ ca^pi^ti*s tri_ste^ be_lli^ge^ri_ le^va*

speaker: ['#satelles']
perseus: et ora matri redde, quo vultus refers
anceps: e*t o_ra^ ma_tri* re_dde^ qvo_ vu*ltu_s re^fe*rs

speaker: ['#satelles']
perseus: acieque pavida fratris observas manum?
anceps: a^ci^e_qve^ pa^vi^da* fra_tri^s o_bse*rva_s ma^nu*m

speaker: ['#satelles']
perseus: affusa totum corpus amplexu tegam,
anceps: a*ffu_sa^ to_tu*m co_rpu^s a_mple*xu_ te^ga*m

speaker: ['#satelles']
perseus: tuo emori per meum fiet via.
anceps: tu*o_ cru^o_ri* pe_r me^u_m fi*e_t vi^a*

speaker: ['#satelles']
perseus: quid dubius haeres? an times matris fidem?
anceps: qvi*d du^bi^u^s h[ae]re*s a_n ti^me_s ma*tri_s fi^de*m

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: Timeo; nihil iam iura naturae valent.
anceps: ti^me^o_ ni^hi_l ja*m ju_ra^ na_tu*r[ae] va^le*nt

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: post ista fratrum exempla ne matri quidem
anceps: po*st i_sta^ fra_tr(u)m e*xe_mpla^ ne_ ma*tri_ qvi^de*m

speaker: ['#polynices', '#iocasta']
perseus: fides habenda est. Redde iam capulo manum,
anceps: fi*de_s ha^be_nd(a) e*st re_dde^ ja_m ca^pu^lo_ ma^nu*m

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: astringe galeam, laeva se clipeo inserat;
anceps: a*stri_nge^ ga^le^a*m l[ae]va^ se_ cli^pe^(o) i_nse^ra*t

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: dum frater exarmatur, armatus mane.
anceps: du*m fra_te^r e_xa*rma_tu^r a_rma*tu_s ma^ne*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: tu pone ferrum, causa qui ferri es prior.
anceps: tu* po_ne^ fe_rru*m c[au]sa^ qvi_ fe*rr(i) e_s pri^o*r

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: si pacis odium est, furere si bello placet:
anceps: si* pa_ci^s o^di^(u)m e*st fu^re^re^ si_ be*llo_ pla^ce*t

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: indutias te mater exiguas rogat,
anceps: i*ndu_ti^a_s te* ma_te^r e_xi^gu^a_s ro^ga*t

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: ferat ut reverso post fugam nato oscula
anceps: fe^ra^t u_t re^ve_rso* po_st fu^ga_m na*t(o) o_scu^la*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: vel prima vel suprema, dum pacem peto,
anceps: ve*l pri_ma^ ve_l su*pre_ma^ du_m pa*ce_m pe^to*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: audite inermes, ille te, tu illum times?
anceps: [au]di_t(e) i^ne_rme*s i_lle^ te_ t(u) i*llu_m ti^me*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: ego utrumque, sed pro utroque, quid strictum abnuis
anceps: e^g(o) u^tru_mqve^ se_d pr(o) u*tro_qve^ qvi_d stri*ct(u)m a_bnu^i*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: recondere ensem? qualibet gaude mora:
anceps: re*co_nde^r(e) e_nse*m qva_li^be_t g[au]de_ mo^ra*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: id gerere bellum cupitis, in quo est optimum
anceps: i*d ge^re^re^ be_llu*m cu^pi^ti^s i_n qv(o) e*st o_pti^mu*m

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: vinci, vereris fratris infesti dolos?
anceps: vi*nci_ ve^re_ri*s fra_tri^s i_nfe*sti_ do^lo*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: quotiens necesse est fallere aut falli a suis,
anceps: qvo^ti^e_ns ne^ce_ss(e) e*st fa_lle^r(e) [au]t fa*ll(i) a_ su^i*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: patiare potius ipse quam facias scelus.
anceps: pa^ti^a_re^ po^ti^u*s i_pse^ qva_m fa^ci^a_s sce^lu*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: sed ne verere: mater insidias et hinc
anceps: se*d ne_ ve^re_re* ma_te^r i_nsi^di^a_s e^t hi*nc

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: et rursus illinc abiget. exoro? an patri
anceps: e*t ru_rsu^s i_lli*nc a^bi^ge^t e_xo*r(o) a_n pa^tri*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: invideo vestro? veni ut arcerem nefas
anceps: i*nui^de^o^ ue_stro* ue_n(i) u^t a_rce*re_m ne^fa*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: an ut viderem propius? hic ferrum abdidit,
anceps: a*n u_t vi^de_re*m pro^pi^u^s hi_c fe*rr(u)m a_bdi^di*t

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: reclinis hasta est, arma defixa incubant.
anceps: re*cli_ni^s ha_st[ae] pa_rma^ de_fi*x(ae) i_ncu^ba*t

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: ad te preces nunc, nate, maternas feram,
anceps: a*d te_ pre^ce_s nu*nc na_te^ ma_te*rna_s fe^ra*m

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: sed ante lacrimas, teneo longo tempore
anceps: se*d a_nte^ la^cri^ma*s te^ne^o^ lo_ngo* te_mpo^re*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: petita votis ora. te profugum solo
anceps: pe*ti_ta^ vo_ti*s o_ra^ te_ pro^fu^gu_m so^lo*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: patrio penates regis externi tegunt.
anceps: pa^tri^o_ pe^na_te*s re_gi^s e_xte*rni_ te^gu*nt

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: te maria tot diversa, tot casus vagum
anceps: te* ma^ri^a^ to_t di*ve_rsa^ to_t ca*su_s va^gu*m

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: egere, non te duxit in thalamos parens
anceps: e*ge_re^ no_n te* du_xi^t i_n tha^la^mo_s pa^re*ns

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: comitata primos nec sua festas manu
anceps: co^mi^ta_ta^ pri_mo*s ne_c su^a_ fe*sta_s ma^nu*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: ornavit aedes nec sacra laetas faces
anceps: o*rna_vi^t [ae]de*s ne_c sa^cra_ l[ae]ta_s fa^ce*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: vitta revinxit; dona non auro graves
anceps: vi*tta_ re^vi_nxi*t do_na^ no_n [au]ro_ gra^ve*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: gazas socer, non arva, non urbes dedit:
anceps: ga*za_s so^ce_r no*n a_rva^ no_n u*rbe_s de^di*t

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: dotale bellum est. hostium es factus gener,
anceps: do*ta_le^ be_ll(u)m e*st ho_sti^(u)m e_s fa*ctu_s ge^ne*r

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: patria remotus hospes alieni laris,
anceps: pa^tri^a_ re^mo_tu*s ho_spe^s a^li^e*ni_ la^ri*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: externa consecutus, expulsus tuis,
anceps: e*xte_rna^ co_nse*cu_tu^s e_xpu*lsu_s tu^i*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: sine crimine exul. ne quid e fatis tibi
anceps: si^ne^ cri_mi^n(e) e_xu*l ne_ qvi^d e_ fa*ti_s ti^bi*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: desset paternis, hoc quoque ex illis habes,
anceps: de*sse_t pa^te_rni*s ho_c qvo^qv(e) e_x i*lli_s ha^be*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: errasse thalamis, nate post multos mihi
anceps: e*rra_sse^ tha^la^mi*s na_te^ po_st mu*lto_s mi^hi*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: remissa soles, nate suspensae metus
anceps: re*mi_sse^ so_le*s na_te^ su_spe*ns[ae] me^tu*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: et spes parentis, cuius aspectum deos
anceps: e*t spe_s pa^re_nti*s cu_ju^s a_spe*ctu_m de^o*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: semper rogavi, cum tuus reditus mihi
anceps: se*mpe_r ro^ga_vi* cu_m tu^u_s re^di^tu_s mi^hi*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: tantum esset erepturus, adventu tuo
anceps: ta*nt(u)m e_sse^t e_re*ptu_ru^s a_dve*ntu_ tu^o*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: quantum daturus: 'quando pro te desinam'
anceps: qva*ntu_m da^tu_ru*s qva_ndo^ pro_ te* de_si^na*m

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: dixi 'timere?' dixit inridens deus:

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: 'ipsum timebis.' nempe nisi bellum foret,
anceps: i*psu_m ti^me_bi*s ne_mpe^ ni^si^ be*llu_m fo^re*t

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: ego te carerem; nempe si tu non fores,
anceps: e^go^ te_ ca^re_re*m ne_mpe^ si_ tu* no_n fo^re*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: bello carerem. a, triste conspectus datur
anceps: be*llo_ ca^re_re*m tri_ste^ co_nspe*ctu_s da^tu*r

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: pretium tui durumque, sed matri placet.
anceps: pre^ti^u_m tu^i_ du*ru_mqve^ se_d ma*tri_ pla^ce*t

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: hinc modo recedant arma, dum nullum nefas
anceps: hi*nc mo^do^ re^ce_da*nt a_rma^ du_m nu*llu_m ne^fa*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: Mars saevus audet: hoc quoque est magnum nefas.
anceps: ma*rs s[ae]vu^s [au]de*t ho_c qvo^qv(e) e_st ma*gnu_m ne^fa*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: tam prope fuisse, stupeo et exsanguis tremo,
anceps: ta*m pro^pe^ fu^i_sse* stu^pe^(o) e^t e_xa*ngvi_s tre^mo*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: cum stare fratres hinc et hinc video duos
anceps: cu*m sta_re^ fra_tre*s hi_nc e^t hi_nc vi^de^o_ du^o*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: sceleris sub ictu. membra quassantur metu:
anceps: sce^le^ri_s su^b i_ctu* me_mbra^ qva_ssa*ntu_r me^tu*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: quam paene mater maius aspexi nefas.
anceps: qva*m p[ae]ne^ ma_te*r ma_ju^s a_spe*xi_ ne^fa*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: quam quod miser videre non potuit pater.
anceps: qva*m qvo_d mi^se_r vi*de_re^ no_n po^tu^i_t pa^te*r

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: licet timore facinoris tanti vacem
anceps: li*ce_t ti^mo_re* fa^ci^no^ri_s ta*nti_ va^ce*m

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: videamque iam nil tale, sum infelix tamen
anceps: vi^de^a_mqve^ ja_m ni*l ta_le^ s(u)m i_nfe*li_x ta^me*n

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: quod paene vidi. per decem mensum graves
anceps: qvo*d p[ae]ne^ vi_di* pe_r de^ce_m me*nsu_m gra^ve*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: uteri labores perque pietatem inclitae
anceps: u^te^ri_ la^bo_re*s pe_rqve^ pi^e^ta*t(e)m i_ncli^t[ae]

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: precor sororis et per irati sibi
anceps: pre*co_r so^ro_ri*s e_t pe^r i_ra*ti_ si^bi*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: genas parentis, scelere quas nullo nocens,
anceps: ge*na_s pa^re_nti*s sce^le^re^ qva_s nu*llo_ no^ce*ns

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: erroris a se dira supplicia exigens,
anceps: e*rro_ri^s a_ se* du_ra^ su_ppli^ci^(a) e_xi^ge*ns

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: hausit: nefandas moenibus patriis faces
anceps: h[au]si_t ne^fa_nda*s m[oe]ni^bu_s pa^tri^i_s fa^ce*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: averte, signa bellici retro agminis
anceps: a*ve_rte^ si_gna* be_lli^ci_ re*tr(o) a_gmi^ni*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: flecte— ut recedas, magna pars sceleris tamen
anceps: fle*ct(e) u_t re^ce_da*s ma_gna^ pa_rs sce^le^ri_s ta^me*n

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: vestri peracta est: vidit hostili grege
anceps: ve*stri_ pe^ra_ct(a) e*st vi_di^t ho_sti*li_ gre^ge*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: campos repleri patria, fulgentes procul
anceps: ca*mpo_s re^ple_ri* pa^tri^a^ fu_lge*nte_s pro^cu*l

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: armis catervas vidit, equitatu levi
anceps: a*rmi_s ca^te_rva*s vi_di^t e^qvi^ta*tu_ le^vi*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: Cadmea frangi prata et excelsos rotis
anceps: ca*dme_a^ fra_ngi* pra_t(a) e^t e_xce*lso_s ro^ti*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: volitare proceres, igne flagrantes trabes
anceps: vo^li^ta_re^ pro^ce^re*s i_gne^ fla_gra*nte_s tra^be*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: fumare, cineri quae petunt nostras domos,
anceps: fu*ma_re^ ci^ne^ri* qv[ae] pe^tu_nt no*stra_s do^mo*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: fratresque (facinus quod novum et Thebis fuit)
anceps: fra*tre_sqve^ fa^ci^nu*s qvo_d no^v(u)m e_t the*bi_s fu^i*t

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: in se ruentes: totus hoc exercitus,
anceps: i*n se_ ru^e_nte*s to_tu^s ho_c e*xe_rci^tu*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: hoc populus omnis, utraque hoc vidit soror
anceps: ho*c po^pu^lu^s o_mni*s u_tra^qv(e) ho_c vi*di_t so^ro*r

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: genetrixque vidi: nam pater debet sibi
anceps: ge^ne^tri_xqve^ vi_di* na_m pa^te_r de*be_t si^bi*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: quod ista non spectavit, occurrat tibi
anceps: qvo*d i_sta^ no_n spe*cta_vi^t o_ccu*rra_t ti^bi*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: nunc Oedipus, quo iudice erroris quoque
anceps: nu*nc [oe]di^pu_s qvo* ju_di^c(e) e_rro*ri_s qvo^qve*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: poenae petuntur. ne, precor, ferro erue
anceps: p[oe]n[ae] pe^tu_ntu*r ne_ pre^co_r fe*rr(o) e_ru^e*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: patriam ac penates neve, quas regere expetis,
anceps: pa^tri^(a)m a_c pe^na_te*s ne_ve^ qv[ae] re^ge^r(e) e_xpe^ti*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: everte Thebas. quis tenet mentem furor?
anceps: e*ve_rte^ the_ba*s qvi_s te^ne_t me*nte_m fu^ro*r

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: petendo patriam perdis? ut fiat tua,.
anceps: pe*te_ndo^ pa^tri^a*m pe_rdi^s u_t fi*a_t tu^a*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: vis esse nullam? quin tuae causae nocet
anceps: vi*s e_sse^ nu_lla*m qvi_n tu^[ae] c[au]s[ae] no^ce*t

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: ipsum hoc quod armis uris infestis solum
anceps: i*ps(u)m ho_c qvo^d a_rmi*s u_ri^s i_nfe*sti_s so^lu*m

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: segetesque adultas sternis et totos fugam
anceps: se^ge^te_sqv(e) a^du_lta*s ste_rni^s e_t to*to_s fu^ga*m

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: edis per agros: nemo sic vastat sua;
anceps: e*di_s pe^r a_gro*s ne_mo^ si_c va*sta_t su^a*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: quae corripi igne. quae meti gladio iubes
anceps: qv[ae] co_rri^p(i) i_gne* qv[ae] me^ti_ gla^di^o_ ju^be*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: aliena credis, rex sit ex vobis uter,
anceps: a^li^e_na^ cre_di*s re_x si^t e_x vo*bi_s u^te*r

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: manente regno quaerite, haec telis petis
anceps: ma*ne_nte^ re_gno* qv[ae]ri^t(e) h[ae]c te*li_s pe^te*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: flammisque tecta? poteris has Amphionis
anceps: fla*mmi_sqve^ te_cta* po^te^ri^s ha_s a*mphi_o^ni*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: quassare moles? nulla quas struxit manus
anceps: qva*ssa_re^ mo_le*s nu_lla^ qva_s stru*xi_t ma^nu*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: stridente tardum machina ducens onus,
anceps: stri*de_nte^ ta_rdu*m ma_chi^na_ du*ce_ns o^nu*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: sed convocatus vocis et citharae sono
anceps: se*d co_nvo^ca_tu*s vo_ci^s e_t ci^tha^r[ae] so^no*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: per se ipse summas venit in turres lapis:
anceps: pe*r s(e) i_pse^ su_mma*s ve_ni^t i_n tu*rre_s la^pi*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: haec saxa franges? victor hinc spolia auferes
anceps: h[ae]c sa_xa^ fra_nge*s vi_cto^r hi_nc spo^li^(a) [au]fe^re*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: vinctosque duces patris aequales tui,
anceps: vi*ncto_sque^ du_ce*s pa_tri^s [ae]qua*le_s tu^i*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: matresque ab ipso coniugum raptas sinu
anceps: ma*tre_sqv(e) a^b i_pso* co_nju^gu_m ra*pta_s si^nu*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: saevus catena miles imposita trahet?
anceps: s[ae]vu_s ca^te_na* mi_le^s i_mpo^si^ta_ tra^he*t

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: adulta virgo, mixta captivo gregi,
anceps: a*du_lta^ vi_rgo* mi_xta^ ca_pti*vo_ gre^gi*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: Thebana nuribus munus Argolicis eat?
anceps: the*ba_na^ nu^ri^bu*s mu_nu^s a_rgo^li^ci_s e^a*t

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: an et ipsa, palmas vincta postergum datas,
anceps: a^n e^t i_psa^ pa_lma*s vi_ncta^ po_ste*rgu_m da^ta*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: mater triumphi praeda fraterni vehar?
anceps: ma*te_r tri^u_mphi* pr[ae]da^ fra_te*rni_ ve^ha*r

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: potesne cives leto et exilio datos
anceps: po*te_sne^ ci_ve*s le_t(o) e^t e_xi^ti^o_ da^to*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: videre passim? moenibus caris potes
anceps: vi*de_re^ pa_ssi*m m[oe]ni^bu_s ca*ri_s po^te*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: hostem admovere, sanguine et flamma potes
anceps: ho*st(e)m a_dmo^ue_re* sa_ngui^n(e) e_t fla*mma_ po^te*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: implere Thebas? tam ferus durum geris
anceps: i*mple_re^ the_ba*s ta_m fe^ru_s du*ru_m ge^ri*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: saevumque in iras pectus? et nondum imperas.
anceps: s[ae]vu_mqv(e) i^n i_ra*s pe_ctu^s e_t no*nd(u)m i_mpe^ra*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: quid sceptra facient? pone vaesanos, precor,
anceps: qvi*d sce_ptra^ fa^ci^e*nt po_ne^ ve_sa*no_s pre^co*r

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: animi tumores teque pietati refer.
anceps: a^ni^mi_ tu^mo_re*s te_qve^ pi^e^ta*ti_ re^fe*r

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: Vt profugus errem? semper ut patria arcear
anceps: u*t pro^fu^gu^s e_rre*m se_mpe^r u_t pa^tri^(a) a_rce^a*r

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: opemque gentis hospes externae sequar?
anceps: o*pe_mqve^ ge_nti*s ho_spe^s e_xte*rn[ae] se^qva*r

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: quid paterer aliud, si fefellissem fidem?
anceps: qvi*d pa^te^re^r a^li^u*d si_ fe^fe_lli*sse_m fi^de*m

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: si peierassem? fraudis alienae dabo
anceps: si* pe_je^ra_sse*m fr[au]di^s a^li^e*n[ae] da^bo*

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: poenas, at ille praemium scelerum feret?
anceps: p[oe]na_s a^t i_lle* pr[ae]mi^u_m sce^le^ru_m fe^re*t

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: iubes abire: matris imperio obsequor—
anceps: ju*be_s a^bi_re* ma_tri^s i_mpe^ri^(o) o_bse^qvo*r

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: da quo revertar, regia frater meus
anceps: da* qvo_ re^ve_rta*r re_gi^a_ fra*te_r me^u*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: habitat superba: parva me abscondat casa?
anceps: ha^bi^te_t su^pe_rba* pa_rva^ m(e) a_bsco*nda_t ca^sa*

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: hanc date repulso; liceat exiguo lare
anceps: ha*nc da_ re^pu_lso* li^ce^a^t e_xi^gu^o_ la^re*

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: pensare regnum? coniugi donum datus
anceps: pe*nsa_re^ re_gnu*m co_nju^gi_ do*nu_m da^tu*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: arbitria thalami dura felicis feram
anceps: a*rbi^tri^a^ tha^la^mi* du_ra^ fe_li*ci_s fe^ra*m

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: humilisque socerum lixa dominantem sequar?
anceps: hu^mi^li_sqve^ so^ce^ru*m li_xa^ do^mi^na*nte_m se^qva*r

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: in servitutem cadere de regno grave est.
anceps: i*n se_rvi^tu_te*m ca^de^re^ de_ re*gno_ gra^v(e) e*st

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: ioc. Si regna quaeris nec potest sceptro manus
anceps: si* re_gna^ qv[ae]ri*s ne_c po^te_st sce*ptro_ ma^nu*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: vacare saevo, multa quae possunt peti
anceps: va*ca_re^ s[ae]vo* mu_lta^ qv[ae] po*ssi_nt pe^ti*

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: in orbe toto quaelibet tellus dabit.
anceps: i*n o_rbe^ to_to* qv[ae]li^be_t te*llu_s da^bi*t

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: hinc nota Baccho Tmolus attollit iuga,
anceps: hi*nc no_ta^ ba_ccho* tmo_lu^s a_tto*lli_t ju^ga*

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: qua lata terris spatia frugiferis iacent
anceps: qva* la_ta^ te_rri*s spa^ti^a^ fru_gi^fe^ri_s ja^ce*nt

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: et qua trahens opulenta Pactolus vada
anceps: e*t qva_ tra^he_ns o^pu^le_nta^ pa_cto*lu_s va^da*

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: inundat auro rura; nec laetis minus
anceps: i*nu_nda^t [au]ro* ru_ra^ ne_c l[ae]ti_s mi^nu*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: Maeandros arvis flectit errantis aquas
anceps: m[ae]a_ndro^s a_rui*s fle_cti^t e_rra*nte_s a^qua*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: rapidusque campos fertiles Hermus secat;
anceps: ra^pi^du_sqve^ ca_mpo*s fe_rti^le_s he*rmu_s se^ca*t

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: hinc grata Cereri Gargara et dives solum
anceps: hi*nc gra_ta^ ce^re^ri* ga_rga^r(a) e_t di*ve_s so^lu*m

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: quod Xanthus ambit nivibus Idaeis tumens;
anceps: qvo*d xa_nthu^s a_mbi*t ni^vi^bu^s i_d[ae]i_s tu^me*ns

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: hinc qua relinquit nomen Ionii mare
anceps: hi*nc qva_ re^li_nqvi*t no_me^n i_o*nji_ ma^re*

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: faucesque Abydo Sestos opposita premit,
anceps: f[au]ce_sqv(e) a^by_do* se_sto^s o_ppo*si^ta^ pre^mi*t

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: aut quae latus iam propior orienti dedit
anceps: [au]t qva_ la^tu_s ja*m pro^pi^u^s o^ri^e*nti_ de^di*t

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: tutamque crebris portibus Lyciam videt:
anceps: tu*ta_mqve^ cre_bri*s po_rti^bu_s ly^ci^a_m vi^de*t

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: haec regna ferro quaere, in hos populos ferat
anceps: ha*c re_gna^ fe_rro* qv[ae]r(e) i^n ho_s po^pu^lo_s fe^ra*t

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: socer arma fortis, has tuo sceptro paret
anceps: so^ce^r a_rma^ fo_rti*s ha_s tu^o_ sce*ptro_ pa^re*t

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: tradatque gentes, hoc adhuc regnum puta
anceps: tra*da_tqve^ ge_nte*s ho_c a^dhu_c re*gnu_m pu^ta*

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: tenere patrem, melius exilium est tibi
anceps: te*ne_re^ pa_tre*m me^li^u^s e_xi^li^(u)m e_st ti^bi*

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: quam reditus iste: crimine alieno exulas,
anceps: qua*m re^di^tu^s i_ste* cri_mi^n(e) a^li^e*n(o) e_xu^la*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: tuo redibis. melius istis viribus
anceps: tu*o_ re^di_bi*s me^li^u^s i_sti*s ui_ri^bu*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: nova regna nullo scelere maculata appetes.
anceps: no^va^ re_gna^ nu_llo* sce^le^re^ ma^cu^la*t(a) a_ppe^te*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: quin ipse frater arma comitatus tua
anceps: qvi*n i_pse^ fra_te*r a_rma^ co^mi^ta*tu_s tu^a*

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: tibi militabit. vade et id bellum gere
anceps: ti^bi^ mi_li^ta_bi*t va_d(e) e^t i_d be*llu_m ge^re*

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: in quo pater materque pugnanti tibi
anceps: i*n qvo_ pa^te_r ma*te_rqve^ pu_gna*nti_ ti^bi*

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: favere possint, regna cum scelere omnibus
anceps: fa*ve_re^ po_ssi*nt re_gna^ cu_m sce^le^r(e) o_mni^bu*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: sunt exilis graviora, nunc belli mala
anceps: su*nt e_xi^li_s gra^ui^o_ra^ nu_nc be*lli_ ma^la*

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: propone, dubias Martis incerti vices:
anceps: pro*po_ne^ du^bi^a*s ma_rti^s i_nce*rti_ vi^ce*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: licet omne tecum Graeciae robur trahas,
anceps: li^ce^t o_mne^ te_cu*m gr[ae]ci^[ae] ro*bu_r tra^ha*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: licet arma longe miles ac late explicet,
anceps: li^ce^t a_rma^ lo_nge* mi_le^s a_c la*t(e) e_xpli^ce*t

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: fortuna belli semper ancipiti in loco est.
anceps: fo*rtu_na^ be_lli* se_mpe^r a_nci^pi^t(i) i_n lo^c(o) e*st

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: quodcumque Mars decernit; exaequat duos,
anceps: qvo*dcu_mqve^ ma_rs de*ce_rni^t e_x[ae]qva_t du^o*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: licet impares sint, gladius; et spes et metus
anceps: li^ce^t i_mpa^re_s si*nt gla^di^u^s e_t spe*s e_t me^tu*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: Fors caeca versat, praemium incertum petis,
anceps: fo*rs c[ae]ca^ ve_rsa*t pr[ae]mi^(u)m i_nce*rtu_m pe^ti*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: certum scelus, favisse fac votis deos
anceps: ce*rtu_m sce^lu_s fa*vi_sse^ fa_c vo*ti_s de^o*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: omnes tuis: cessere et aversi fugam
anceps: o*mne_s tu^i_s ce*sse_r(e) e^t a_ve*rsi_ fu^ga*m

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: petiere cives, clade funesta iacens
anceps: pe^ti^e_re^ ci_ve*s cla_de^ fu_ne*sta_ ja^ce*ns

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: obtexit agros miles— exultes licet
anceps: o*bte_xi^t a_gro*s mi_le^s e_xu*lte_s li^ce*t

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: victorque fratris spolia deiecti geras:
anceps: vi*cto_rqve^ fra_tri*s spo^li^a^ de_je*cti_ ge^ra*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: frangenda palma est. quale tu hoc bellum putas,
anceps: fra*nge_nda^ pa_lm(a) e*st qva_le^ t(u) ho_c be*llu_m pu^ta*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: in quo execrandum victor admittit nefas,
anceps: i*n qv(o) e_xe^cra_ndu*m vi_cto^r a_dmi*tti_t ne^fa*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: si gaudet? hunc quem vincere infelix cupis,
anceps: si* g[au]de^t hu_nc qve*m vi_nce^r(e) i_nfe*li_x cu^pi*s

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: cum viceris, lugebis. infaustas age
anceps: cu*m vi_ce^ri_s lu*ge_bi^s i_nf[au]sta_s a^ge*

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: dimitte pugnas, libera patriam metu,
anceps: di*mi_tte^ pu_gna*s li_be^ra_ pa^tri^a_m me^tu*

speaker: ['#polynices', '#polynices']
perseus: luctu parentes, Sceleris et fraudis suae
anceps: lu*ctu_ pa^re_nte*s sce^le^ri^s e_t fr[au]di_s su^[ae]

speaker: ['#polynices']
perseus: poenas nefandus frater ut nullas ferat?
anceps: p[oe]na_s ne^fa_ndu*s fra_te^r u_t nu*lla_s fe^ra*t

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: Ne metue. poenas et quidem solvet graves:
anceps: ne* me^tu^e^ p[oe]na*s e_t qvi^de_m so*lve_t gra^ve*s

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: regnabit, est haec poena, si dubitas, avo
anceps: re*gna_bi^t e_st h[ae]c p[oe]na^ si_ du^bi^ta_s a^vo*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: patrique crede: Cadmus hoc dicet tibi
anceps: pa*tri_qve^ cre_de* ca_dmu^s ho_c di*ce_t ti^bi*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: Cadmique proles, sceptra Thebano fuit
anceps: ca*dmi_qve^ pro_le*s sce_ptra^ the_ba*ru_m fu^i*t

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: impune nulli gerere, nec quisquam fide
anceps: i*mpu_ne^ nu_lli* ge^re^re^ ne_c qvi*sqva_m fi^de*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: rupta tenebit illa: iam numeres licet
anceps: ru*pta_ te^ne_ba*t i_lla^ ja_m nu^me^re_s li^ce*t

speaker: ['#iocasta', '#eteocles']
perseus: fratrem inter istos. Numeret, est tanti mihi
anceps: fra*tr(e)m i_nte^r i_sto*s nu^me^re^t e_st ta*nti_ mi^hi*

speaker: ['#eteocles']
perseus: cum regibus iacere, te turbae exulum
anceps: cu*m re_gi^bu_s ja*ce_re^ te_ tu*rb(ae) e_xu^lu*m

speaker: ['#eteocles', '#polynices']
perseus: ascribo. Regna, dummodo invisus tuis.
anceps: a*scri_bo^ re_gna* du_mmo^d(o) i_nvi*su_s tu^i*s

speaker: ['#eteocles']
perseus: Regnare non vult esse qui invisus timet:
anceps: re*gna_re^ no_n vu*lt e_sse^ qv(i) i_nvi*su_s ti^me*t

speaker: ['#eteocles']
perseus: simul ista mundi conditor posuit deus,
anceps: si^mu^l i_sta^ mu_ndi* co_ndi^to_r po^su^i_t de^u*s

speaker: ['#eteocles']
perseus: odium atque regnum: regis hoc magni reor,
anceps: o^di^(u)m a_tqve^ re_gnu*m re_gi^s ho_c ma*gni_ re^o*r

speaker: ['#eteocles']
perseus: odia ipsa premere, multa dominantem vetat
anceps: o^di^(a) i_psa^ pre^me^re* mu_lta^ do^mi^na*nte_m ve^ta*t

speaker: ['#eteocles']
perseus: amor suorum; plus in iratos licet,
anceps: a*mo_r su^o_ru*m plu_s i^n i_ra*to_s li^ce*t

speaker: ['#eteocles']
perseus: qui vult amari, languida regnat manu.
anceps: qvi* vu_lt a^ma_ri* la_ngvi^da_ re*gna_t ma^nu*

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: Invisa numquam imperia retinentur diu.
anceps: i*nvi_sa^ nu_mqv(a)m i*mpe^ri^a^ re^ti^ne*ntu_r di^u*

speaker: ['#eteocles']
perseus: Praecepta melius imperi reges dabunt;
anceps: pr[ae]ce_pta^ me^li^u*s i_mpe^ri_ re*ge_s da^bu*nt

speaker: ['#eteocles']
perseus: exilia tu dispone, pro regno velim—
anceps: e*xi^li^a^ tu_ co*mpo_ne^ pro_ re*gno_ ve^li*m

speaker: ['#iocasta']
perseus: Patriam penates coniugem flammis dare?
anceps: pa^tri^a_m pe^na_te*s co_nju^ge_m fla*mmi_s da^re*

speaker: ['#eteocles']
perseus: Imperia pretio quolibet constant bene.
anceps: i*mpe^ri^a^ pre^ti^o* qvo_li^be_t co*nsta_nt be^ne*
